A group-based behavioural intervention for weight management (PROGROUP) versus 
usual care in adults with severe obesity: a feasibility randomised controlled 
trial protocol.

Swancutt D(1), Tarrant M(2), Ingram W(1), Baldrey S(3), Burns L(1), Byng R(1), 
Calitri R(4), Creanor S(4), Dean S(4), Evans L(4), Gill L(1), Goodwin E(4), 
Hawkins L(4), Hayward C(1), Hind S(3), Hollands L(4), Hosking J(1), Lloyd J(4), 
Moghadam S(4), Neilens H(5), O'Kane M(6), Perry S(7), Sheaff R(1), Spencer A(4), 
Taylor A(1), Ward T(4), Watkins R(4), Wilding J(8), Pinkney J(1).

Author information:
(1)University of Plymouth, Faculty of Health, University of Plymouth, Plymouth 
Science Park, Plymouth, PL6 8BX, UK.
(2)University of Exeter, College of Medicine and Health, St Luke's Campus, 
Heavitree Road, Exeter, EX1 2LU, UK. M.Tarrant@exeter.ac.uk.
(3)Livewell South West, Cumberland Centre, Damerel Close, Devonport, Plymouth, 
PL1 4JZ, UK.
(4)University of Exeter, College of Medicine and Health, St Luke's Campus, 
Heavitree Road, Exeter, EX1 2LU, UK.
(5)University Hospitals Plymouth NHS Trust, Bircham Park Offices, 1 Roscoff 
Rise, Derriford, Plymouth, PL6 5FP, UK.
(6)Leeds Teaching Hospital NHS Trust, St James's University Hospital, Beckett 
Street, Leeds, LS9 7TF, UK.
(7)Independent Consultant, Plymouth, UK.
(8)University of Liverpool, Department of Cardiovascular and Metabolic Medicine, 
Clinical Sciences Centre, Aintree University Hospital, Longmoor Lane, Liverpool, 
